  "text": "It is obvious that if cell-based assays are used, two types of information can be obtained [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] : 1. The toxic effect of individual compounds on the body when samples containing just this one component are tested (reference samples). 2. The endocrine genotoxicity or cytotoxicity effects of environmental or biological samples with an unknown composition are estimated; in this case further types of summary parameters can be referred to for preliminary assessment of the presence of compounds inducing specific toxic effects in samples.",
